---
description: Rust engine conventions — applied when editing engine crate Rust files.
globs: ["blink-engine/crates/**/*.rs"]
alwaysApply: false
---

## Price and size
- Hot path: `u64 × 1000`. Never `f64` in `order_book`, `sniffer`, `ws_client`.
- Use `parse_price()` / `format_price()` from `types.rs` — never parse manually.

## Error handling
- `anyhow::Result` for app errors, `thiserror` for typed library errors.
- Never `.unwrap()` in non-test code. Propagate with `?`. Log with `tracing::error!` before returning.

## Concurrency — match primitive to context
- `tokio::sync::Mutex` — held across `.await` points (portfolio, signal queue)
- `std::sync::Mutex` — short sync-only critical sections (risk manager, drift cooldown)
- `Arc<AtomicU64>` / `AtomicBool` — lock-free counters/flags
- `crossbeam_channel` — hot-path signal passing (lock-free bounded MPSC)

## Module structure
- Every module: `//!` doc comment with purpose + hot/cold classification
- Cold-path modules: add `//! **Latency class: COLD PATH. Never call from signal → order hot path.**`
- `from_env()` on every config struct — `unwrap_or(safe_default)`, never panic
- `main.rs` wires only. All business logic in modules.

## Logging
- `tracing::info!(field = %val, "msg")` — always structured. Never `println!`.

## Testing
- Test pass case AND rejection/error case for every new gate
- `exit_strategy::evaluate_exits()` must remain pure — proptest it

## Dependencies
- Never add versions in crate `Cargo.toml` — always `{ workspace = true }`
